Popular socialite, Pascal Okechukwu fondly called Cubana Chief Priest has been appointed as the social media aide to the Governor of Imo State, Hope Uzodinma. The club owner who is also known as Celebrity Barman took to his verified Instagram account to make the announcement. The Governor of Imo State made the socialite his special adviser on social media influence and social events management. Gov. Ugwuanyi inaugurates multiple projects in IMT Enugu Twitter regulations attempt to suppress constitutional rights – Reps minority caucus Okechukwu uploaded a picture with the Deputy Speaker of the Imo Assembly, Amarachi Iwuanyanwu holding his appointment letter. He said, “Just picked up my letter of appointment as special adviser to His Excellency, Hope Uzodinma, on social media influence and social events management. I have an instruction from his excellency to make over 1,000 Imo youths get super successful like me from the almighty social media which made me in just one year, it’s so easy for me to do and I will do just that through Christ who strengthens me Amen. May God give me the grace, wisdom, energy and guts to tell his excellency the unfiltered truth he needs to hear at all times Amen.”(sic) See post below: 